      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "**Description**\n",
        "\n",
        "This dataset is about using brainwave signals to detect confusion in students during online learning. It contains EEG recordings from 10 college students who watched a series of 20 educational video clips.\n",
        "\n",
        "These videos were split into two categories:\n",
        "\n",
        "- Non-confusing videos: Simple topics like basic algebra.\n",
        "\n",
        "- Confusing videos: Complex topics like Quantum Mechanics, which were edited abruptly to make them harder to follow.\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "The students wore a wireless headset that measured brain activity from the forehead. The dataset provides two ways to classify the data: the predefined category of the video (was it supposed to be confusing?) and the student's self-reported rating (did they actually feel confused?).\n",
        "\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "3nmjWfx-DgA7"
      }
    },
