    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "From the plot above, we can see tht there are high correlation between Beta 2 and Gamma1, as well as Gamma 1 and Gamma 2.\n",
        "\n",
        "**Why might this be?**\n",
        "The high correlation between Beta2 and Gamma1 suggests that these brainwave frequencies are often co-activated during intense cognitive processing. Beta waves (13-30 Hz) are associated with alertness and active thinking, while Gamma waves (30-100 Hz) are linked to higher-level cognitive functions like focus and learning. Therefore, when subjects are engaged in demanding mental tasks, such as those that might induce confusion, both these frequency bands tend to increase together.\n",
        "\n"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "anM4CnyEH0HM"
      }
