      "source": [
        "# Different Models\n",
        "\n",
        "Build and evaluate Neural Network, KNN (K-Nearest Neighbors), and Logistic Regression models to predict student confusion based on EEG data. We will then compare the performance of these models and identify the best-performing one using metrics like accuracy, precision, recall, and F1-score."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Naive Neural Network\n",
        "import tensorflow as tf\n",
        "\n",
        "# Set random seed for reproducibility\n",
        "tf.random.set_seed(42)\n",
        "\n",
        "model = tf.keras.models.Sequential([\n",
        "    tf.keras.layers.Dense(128, activation='relu', input_shape=(X_train.shape[1],)),\n",
        "    tf.keras.layers.Dense(64, activation='relu'),\n",
